org.spongepowered.api.event.item.inventory

Interface DropItemEvent

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cancellable, Event
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ClickInventoryEvent.Drop, ClickInventoryEvent.Drop.Full, ClickInventoryEvent.Drop.Outside, ClickInventoryEvent.Drop.Outside.Creative, ClickInventoryEvent.Drop.Outside.Primary, ClickInventoryEvent.Drop.Outside.Secondary, ClickInventoryEvent.Drop.Single, DropItemEvent.Close, DropItemEvent.Custom, DropItemEvent.Destruct, DropItemEvent.Dispense, DropItemEvent.Pre

    public interface DropItemEvent
extends Event, Cancellable
    Handles when one or more Item or ItemStack are about to be "dropped" onto the ground. This will happen before they are physically dropped, let alone spawned.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  DropItemEvent.Close
      Called whenever an Item is dispensed by closing a Container.
      static interface  DropItemEvent.Custom
      Called whenever an Item is dropped from another source.
      static interface  DropItemEvent.Destruct
      Called when one or more Item drops are triggered by an object such as an Entity or BlockType destruction.
      static interface  DropItemEvent.Dispense
      Called whenever an Item is dispensed from a type of Inventory such as a Player or Container.
      static interface  DropItemEvent.Pre
      Handles ItemStacks and may be called before an Item entity is actually constructed.
